{"article_id":"yk3fZ7HyfbHGaAmF","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"Gov . Scott Walker beats challenger Tom Barrett by a 53 % -46 % margin","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"Walker 's margin of victory larger than 2010 race","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"in which he also faced Barrett","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Democrats spurred the recall effort over Walker 's efforts","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"to weaken public unions","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Tens of millions of dollars have poured in from outside the state , mostly for Walker","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"In a vote","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that could have implications on both the November presidential race and for organized labor ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"Wisconsin Gov . Scott Walker on Tuesday successfully overcame a recall vote","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that would have removed him from office .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"With almost all of the votes in , Walker , a Republican hero","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"for pushing austerity measures","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"that stripped collective bargaining rights from most public unions ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"led Milwaukee Mayor Tom Barrett by a 53-46 margin .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Tuesday 's vote was the culmination of a 15-month near-civil war","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that pitted unions and Democratic supporters against fiscal conservatives and Republicans","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"after Walker signed a bill in March 2011","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"passed by the Republican-controlled legislature","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"that took collective bargaining rights away from public employee unions in a effort","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"to close the state 's budget gap .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"Tens of thousands of demonstrators","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"opposing Walker","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"crowded the grounds around the state capitol","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"and hung banners of protest in its rotunda","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"after Walker signed the bill","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and kicked off a recall drive","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"that gathered 900,000 signatures","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"-- nearly 400,000 more than required .","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"During a bitter fight over the law last year , Democratic legislators left the capital","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"to prevent a quorum .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Union members upset over Walker victory","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"MUST WATCH Union members upset over Walker victory","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"01:41","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"JUST WATCHED Walker :","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"'Time to move Wisconsin forward '","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"MUST WATCH Walker :","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"'Time","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"to move Wisconsin forward '","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"02:29","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Politician slapped in the face","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"MUST WATCH Politician slapped in the face 00:46","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"In declaring victory on Tuesday ,","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Walker said","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"the outcome validated his hard line on cost-cutting .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"`` Tonight , we tell Wisconsin ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"we tell our country","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"and we tell people all across the globe","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that voters really do want leaders","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"who stand up","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"and make the tough decisions , ''","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"he told a roaring crowd at his campaign headquarters in Waukesha .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"He also addressed the polarized climate in the normally centrist state","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"-- his crowd jeered","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"when he mentioned","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that he had a phone conversation with Barrett","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"before taking the stage .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"`` Bringing our state together will take some time","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"-- there 's just no doubt about it , ''","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"But he offered a first step","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"by inviting members of the legislature over for bratwursts and burgers , `` and then maybe a little bit of good Wisconsin beer , as well . ''","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"In conceding ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Barrett also drew catcalls","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"when he mentioned the call with Walker .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"And he said","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"it was important that he and the governor work together .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"`` This is not an end , ''","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"`` Tonight ends another chapter in Wisconsin history","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"but there 's more to come . ''","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Unions pointed to Walker supporters","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"' outspending his opponents by a more than 7-1 margin , 70 % of it from outside the state .","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"`` Adding to this gargantuan challenge","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"of recalling only the third governor in American history","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"was the flood of secret corporate cash","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"distorting our democracy","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"-- a dangerous example of a post-Citizens United America , ''","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"AFL-CIO president Richard Trumka said in a statement after the vote ,","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"referring to the Supreme Court decision","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"that allowed unlimited political contributions from corporations and unions .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Both parties cast the debate as a larger referendum on the role of government and policies","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"supported by both parties .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"While political pundits framed the race as a test run for the presidential election ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"fiscal conservatives were looking for momentum in a growing movement","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"to curb what they see as public employee unions","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"getting larded with benefits from politicians","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"that they helped elect .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"`` ( Walker 's ) one of the Republican governors","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"who has been out on the point on this issue","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"about whether there are excesses in public employee unions in terms of their pension plans or health care plans and so forth , ''","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"CNN political analyst David Gergen said .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"`` This is a very , very hot issue from New York to California and from New Jersey to Indiana to Ohio to Wisconsin . ``","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"And this election tonight was well-regarded long before by both sides as the second most important election of the year .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"And here Scott Walker ,","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"I must say ,","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"to a surprise ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"given a year ago ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"it looked like he was going to lose this , tonight ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"to win is a substantial defeat for labor , for public employee unions , and a substantial defeat -- a substantial victory for those","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"who have been trying to curb them . ''","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Public opinion polls","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"leading up to the vote","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"had shown Walker holding a narrowing lead","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"and early exit polls suggested","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"the race would be tight ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"with 34 % of those responding identifying themselves as Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"35 % saying","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"they 're Republicans","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"and 31 % saying","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"they 're independents .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"A state official said on condition","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"of not being identified","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"that turnout appeared to be strong ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"with reports of some polling places","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"running out of forms for same-day voter registration .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"The race was a rematch of the 2010 governor 's contest ,","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"won by Walker with only 52 % of the vote .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"JUST WATCHED Obama skipping Wisconsin recall vote ?","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"MUST WATCH Obama skipping Wisconsin recall vote ?","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"01:27","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"JUST WATCHED Wisconsin recall :","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"Dry run for November","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"MUST WATCH Wisconsin recall :","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Dry run for November 04:23","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"The first-term governor 's win could give Republicans a major boost in efforts","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"to make Wisconsin a battleground state in the November presidential election .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"It now has a strong ground operation in a state","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"that has been remained blue since 1988 .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"But exit polls indicate","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"that the vote Tuesday was n't the presidential litmus test","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"that many pundits suggested .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"While Barrett went down to defeat ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"those","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"responding to exit polls","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"favored President Barack Obama over GOP presumptive presidential nominee Mitt Romney by a 51-44 margin .","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"And Obama got higher marks than Romney on handling the economy by a slim margin and on helping the middle class by a wider margin .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"Obama easily won the state in 2008 ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"but Walker 's unyielding commitment to fiscal austerity in the face of chaotic protests last year made him the poster child for tea party conservatism .","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"Walker would have been only the third governor in U.S. history","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"ousted by a recall election .","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Along with the gubernatorial recall , Lt. Gov . Rebecca Kleefisch also won her recall election .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"Four Republican senators also faced recall votes Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"but results were not yet available .","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"A loss of any of those four races would have tipped control of the Senate to Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"but with the legislature out of session until after the general election , a Democratic win would have provided mostly a moral victory .","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"A former Republican state senator","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"ousted in a Wisconsin recall vote last year","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"said Tuesday","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"that the political wound","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"he suffered","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"was worth it","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"because of the fiscal austerity","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"achieved .","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"`` I lost my job","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"standing for something ,","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"and I was standing for the people , fiscal responsibility and the future of this country and the state and its residents , ''","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"Dan Kapanke said ,","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"that `` the times dictate tough decisions ,","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"and we want our elected officials to do the right thing","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"and worry about the future","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"and not just about the next election . ''","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"Walker complains","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"that repeated recall efforts over past years are stalling progress","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"and costing the state needed money .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"Earlier Tuesday , Barrett said","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"he agrees","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"that voters are tired of recall politics ,","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"but he blamed Walker for creating a divisive political environment","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"that inspired the effort","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"to oust him .","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"`` What Gov . Walker does n't say","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"is he was the one","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"who ,","depth":16},{"id":182,"text":"these are his words ,","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"dropped the bomb","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"and attempted to divide and conquer .","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"So he set out on a strategy","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"to divide this state .","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"He succeeded","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"in dividing the state , ''","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"Barrett said ,","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"that the proper course now is to `` get rid of the instigator","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"rather than to allow him to continue","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"because I think","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"this state will remain this bitterly divided","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"if he continues in office . ''","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"About $ 64 million has been spent on the race since November ,","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"an analysis from the Center for Public Integrity found .","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"That 's a state record ,","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"shattering the record of $ 37.4 million","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"spent during the 2010 governor 's race .","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"Walker collected $ 30.5 million to Barrett 's $ 4 million .","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"Roughly two-thirds of Walker 's contributions came from out of state ,","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"the Center for Public Integrity reported ,","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"while only a quarter of Barrett 's funds originated from outside Wisconsin .","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"Barrett said Tuesday","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"that such outside influence is a change for Wisconsin .","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"`` What 's happened is , Scott Walker has become the rock star of the far right","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"and has been able to raise literally millions of dollars from out-of-state contributors , ''","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"Barrett said .","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"During a bitter fight over the law last year , Democratic legislators left the capital","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"to prevent a quorum ,","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"and tens of thousands of protesters converged on the State Capitol building","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"in what became an occupation .","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"After the law was signed ,","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"Democrats immediately began a recall effort","depth":10},{"id":216,"text":"that led to Tuesday 's vote .","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"Walker has defended his budget actions as necessary for the fiscal health of his state","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"and described his campaign as one of a strong leader","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"who is making the necessary `` tough decisions . ''","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"The campaign has been fierce ,","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"with campaigners complaining of keyed cars , verbal harassment and a general lack of tolerance for differing opinions . `` We have an example of Hatfields and McCoys","depth":15},{"id":222,"text":"going on in this state","depth":15},{"id":223,"text":"like we have never seen , ''","depth":14},{"id":224,"text":"said Brian Nemoir , a Milwaukee-based Republican strategist .","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"`` People are hyper-engaged , as much in support for their own candidate as in disgust for the opponent . ''","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"Handmade signs were nearly as prevalent as official ones .","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"Some locals say","depth":12},{"id":228,"text":"they have resorted to lowering their voices in public","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"when discussing the recall","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"to avoid setting off arguments with strangers .","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"The Justice Department on Monday dispatched federal observers","depth":10},{"id":232,"text":"to monitor Milwaukee polling places Tuesday","depth":11},{"id":233,"text":"to ensure","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"that no voter discrimination took place .","depth":12},{"id":235,"text":"A litany of Republican stars have campaigned for Walker ,","depth":6},{"id":236,"text":"including fellow governors Chris Christie of New Jersey , Nikki Haley of South Carolina , Bobby Jindal of Louisiana and Bob McDonnell of Virginia , as well as U.S. Sen. Marco Rubio from Florida .","depth":6},{"id":237,"text":"While Romney did n't campaign for Walker in Wisconsin ,","depth":8},{"id":238,"text":"he quickly congratulated the governor after his victory .","depth":9},{"id":239,"text":"`` Governor Walker has demonstrated over the past year what sound fiscal policies can do","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"to turn an economy around ,","depth":12},{"id":241,"text":"and I believe","depth":12},{"id":242,"text":"that in November voters across the country will demonstrate","depth":13},{"id":243,"text":"that they want the same in Washington , D.C. , ''","depth":13},{"id":244,"text":"Romney said in a statement .","depth":10},{"id":245,"text":"Americans for Prosperity , a conservative advocacy group","depth":9},{"id":246,"text":"built around many of the same principles as the tea party ,","depth":9},{"id":247,"text":"has pumped more than $ 10 million into Wisconsin","depth":9},{"id":248,"text":"backing Walker 's policies .","depth":9},{"id":249,"text":"Barrett , meanwhile , got his own high-powered support from former President Clinton , as well as Democratic National Committee Chairwoman Debbie Wasserman Schultz and Maryland Gov . Martin O'Malley .","depth":8},{"id":250,"text":"However , his campaign fund-raising has badly trailed the support","depth":10},{"id":251,"text":"Walker received .","depth":10},{"id":252,"text":"The Progressive Change Campaign Committee announced Saturday","depth":10},{"id":253,"text":"that it was spending $ 100,000 in the five days before the Wisconsin recall vote ,","depth":11},{"id":254,"text":"bringing its investment to $ 300,000 .","depth":11},{"id":255,"text":"Obama never came to Wisconsin","depth":11},{"id":256,"text":"to campaign for Barrett ,","depth":11},{"id":257,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":258,"text":"Republicans surmised","depth":12},{"id":259,"text":"was because the president believes","depth":12},{"id":260,"text":"Barrett will lose .","depth":12},{"id":261,"text":"On Sunday , Barrett said on CNN 's `` State of the Union ''","depth":12},{"id":262,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":263,"text":"his campaign never asked Obama to appear on his behalf ,","depth":11},{"id":264,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":265,"text":"that `` we understand","depth":12},{"id":266,"text":"he 's got a lot going on . ''","depth":12},{"id":267,"text":"White House Press Secretary Jay Carney acknowledged the uniqueness of the contest","depth":9},{"id":268,"text":"while stressing","depth":11},{"id":269,"text":"there 's no doubt","depth":12},{"id":270,"text":"where the president stood .","depth":12},{"id":271,"text":"`` The president 's made clear all along his opposition to those","depth":14},{"id":272,"text":"who would take away workers rights","depth":14},{"id":273,"text":"-- to actions","depth":14},{"id":274,"text":"that would take away or diminish worker 's rights , ''","depth":14},{"id":275,"text":"Carney said .","depth":12},{"id":276,"text":"`` And he 's also made clear his support for Tom Barrett . ''","depth":11},{"id":277,"text":"Four Republican senators also faced recall votes Tuesday","depth":3},{"id":278,"text":"but results were not yet available .","depth":3},{"id":279,"text":"A loss of any of those four races would have tipped control of the Senate to Democrats ,","depth":3},{"id":280,"text":"but with the legislature out of session until after the general election , a Democratic win would have provided mostly a moral victory .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":561,"left":557,"right":560,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":557,"left":366,"right":556,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":366,"left":356,"right":365,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":356,"left":284,"right":355,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":284,"left":0,"right":283,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":283,"left":1,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":282,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":355,"left":310,"right":354,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":310,"left":286,"right":309,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":285,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity"